6 <Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.1 Definitions.
7 As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise
8 requires:
9 1. “Countable income” means the income of an individual when
10 the income is received and can be used to meet the individual’s
11 needs for food, clothing, and shelter. “Countable income” does
12 not include the income of another member of the individual’s
13 household, or certain receipts as described in 20 C.F.R.
14 §416.1103.
15 2. “Department” means the department of health and human
16 services.
17 3. “Disability” means a qualifying disability as determined
18 by the federal social security administration, or the
19 individual is determined by the department to have a physical
20 or mental impairment, or combination of impairments, that have
21 lasted or are expected to last for at least twelve months or
22 result in death.
23 4. “Long-term services and supports” means the broad
24 range of health, health-related, and personal care assistance
25 services and supports, provided in home and community-based
26 settings, necessary for persons with disabilities who
27 experience limitations in their capacity for self-care due to a
28 physical, cognitive, or mental disability or condition.
29 5. “Program” means the work without worry program
30 established in section 249O.3.
31 Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.2 Program —— intent.
32 It is the intent of the general assembly to remove barriers
33 to employment for individuals who, but for income and
34 resources, meet the definition of disability, by providing
35 medical assistance to employed individuals with disabilities
