1 through a work without worry program in accordance with section
2 1902(a)(10)(A)(ii)(XIII) of the federal Social Security Act,
3 and Medicaid eligibility, using less restrictive income and
4 resource requirements through the application of section
5 1902(r)(2) of the federal Social Security Act, and cost-sharing
6 requirements established by the department and approved by the
7 centers for Medicare and Medicaid services of the United States
8 department of health and human services.
9 Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.3 Program —— established.
10 1. The work without worry program is established under the
11 medical assistance program and shall be administered by the
12 department to provide employed individuals with disabilities
13 access to health care coverage through the medical assistance
14 program.
15 2. Except as otherwise specified in this chapter,
16 provisions applicable to the medical assistance program
17 pursuant to chapter 249A shall be applicable to the program.
18 3. In addition to the benefits received under the program,
19 an individual shall have access to all traditional Medicaid
20 services under the medical assistance program, as well as
21 additional long-term services and supports and community-based
22 services, including waiver services, for which the individual
23 meets any applicable level of care requirements.
24 4. The department shall make every effort to coordinate
25 benefits with the health care coverage provided by an employer
26 of an employed individual with a disability receiving benefits
27 under this chapter.
28 Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.4 Program —— eligibility.
29 1. Except as otherwise provided in this chapter, an
30 individual may participate in the program if the individual
31 meets all of the following criteria:
32 a. The individual is eligible for the medical assistance
33 program under chapter 249A.
34 b. The individual is at least eighteen years of age.
35 c. The individual is less than sixty-five years of age.
