1 d. The individual has a disability.
2 e. The individual is employed, earns income from employment
3 which may include self-employment, and works at least one hour
4 per month.
5 2. The department shall not adopt a rule for program
6 eligibility based upon any of the following:
7 a. An individual’s income or resources.
8 b. A resource test or limit.
9 c. An individual’s receipt of federal disability benefits.
10 3. An individual who receives supplemental security
11 income shall be automatically eligible for the program and may
12 participate in the program.
13 4. An individual may be eligible for or receive other health
14 care coverage including through an employer, through Medicare,
15 or through the medically needy program, the qualified Medicare
16 beneficiary program, or the specified low-income Medicare
17 beneficiary program. If the individual has such other coverage
18 and is subject to payment of copayments or premiums for that
19 coverage, notwithstanding the premium requirements under the
20 program to the contrary, the individual shall not be subject to
21 payment of premiums otherwise applicable under the program.
22 Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.5 Program —— premiums.
23 1. An individual’s monthly program premium amount shall
24 equal, rounded down to the nearest whole dollar, any of the
25 following:
26 a. If the individual’s verified countable income is less
27 than one hundred fifty percent of the federal poverty level
28 applicable to the individual’s household’s size, zero percent
29 of the individual’s verified countable income.
30 b. If the individual’s verified countable income is between
31 one hundred fifty percent and two hundred fifty percent of
32 the federal poverty level applicable to the individual’s
33 household’s size, three percent of the individual’s verified
34 countable income.
35 c. If the individual’s verified countable income is more
