1 than two hundred fifty percent of the federal poverty level
2 applicable to the individual’s household’s size, six percent of
3 the individual’s verified countable income.
4 2. a. An individual shall report any change in the
5 individual’s countable income to the department.
6 b. The department shall utilize the individual’s verified
7 countable income until the individual reports a change in
8 countable income and the change is processed by the department,
9 unless there is good cause for the department’s delay in
10 verifying the change in the individual’s countable income.
11 c. A change in an individual’s program premium amount shall
12 be effective the month after the change in the individual’s
13 countable income is reported to and verified by the department.
14 3. An individual shall be covered under the program for
15 six consecutive months beginning the first day of the month in
16 which the department approves the individual’s application for
17 the program.
18 4. The department shall create a six-month grace period that
19 provides continuous program coverage to an individual following
20 the individual’s temporary loss of employment, or a health
21 crisis that temporarily prevents the individual from continuing
22 employment. The individual shall be required to continue to
23 pay the program premium based on the individual’s verified
24 countable income during the six-month grace period.
25 5. The department may terminate an individual’s program
26 coverage if the individual fails to pay four consecutive months
27 of program premiums.
28 6. An individual must pay a program premium in full for any
29 month that program coverage is provided, including a month when
30 a redetermination of coverage is made, a month when continued
31 coverage is requested, and during the period of an eligibility
32 determination appeal.
33 Sec. ___. NEW SECTION. 249O.6 Rules.
34 The department shall adopt rules pursuant to chapter 17A to
35 administer this chapter.
